node.text: I had a lovely rest/bad weather/sport climbing day with @renan_ozturk the other day. With rain all over we drove to a different valley, sampled a few pitches, then noticed a via ferrata nearby and climbed it as well. I kind of love via ferratas - the position and experience of soloing with very little of the risk. They’re incredible ways to play in the mountains.

node.text:
A tale of adventure in 3 pics, featuring @korra_pesce and @nicolashojac:⁣
- “Sure looks like a lot of rime ice on that wall, is this really worth climbing right now?!”⁣
- “Ah, here’s the route, maybe it’s better around the corner.”⁣
- “The view from the summit sure made the freezing temps and iced over rock worth it!!”⁣
⁣
We climbed the Dent du Geant, normally a very easy and classic little summit, in very marginal conditions and had what felt like a Patagonian experience.
